threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI5 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, BuildID[sha1]=5cc190ea6cc354029b3a030b41a9bcde98613e12, for GNU/Linux 3.2.0, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a sophisticated Mirai-style IoT botnet variant designed for DDoS attacks and lateral movement. It exhibits multiple malicious behaviors including competition killing (terminating rival botnets by scanning /proc/net/tcp and /proc), daemonization, and process renaming to evade detection. It contains specialized scanning modules for exploiting Realtek SDK vulnerabilities via UPnP SOAP requests (AddPortMapping). The sample includes a comprehensive suite of DDoS attack vectors such as TCP SYN/ACK floods, UDP plain/raknet/vse floods, and GRE floods. It connects to a hardcoded Command and Control (C2) server at 139.162.20.230.
